Spiced Cranberry Muffins

Pears:
2 ripe bartlett pears - peeled, cored, and cut into eighths
1/2 tbsp vanilla
1/2 tsp kosher salt

Preheat oven to 350F and line a baking sheet with foil. Toss the pears with the vanilla and salt directly on the baking sheet, and roast in the oven until soft, 30-35 min. Place the pears in a medium bowl and roughly mash with a whisk for form a mildly chunky paste. Allow to compltely cool and reserve for later.

Muffins:
2 c ap flour
2 c granulated sugar
1/4 c light brown sugar
1 tsp baking powder
1 tsp ground black pepper
1tsp salt
3/4 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp ginger powder
roast pear mixture
3 eggs
12 tbsp unsalted butter, melted
1 c (5oz) cranberries, roughly chopped
1/4 c flaxseeds + more for garnish
1/4 c sliced almonds + more for garnish

Line a standard muffin tin with liners and set aside. In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, sugars, baking powder, pepper, salt, baking soda, and ginger, then set aside. Add eggs and butter to cooled pears. Then add the liquid to the dry and stir until fully incorporated. Fold in the cranberries, flaxseeds, and sliced almonds. Divide the batter among the muffin liners and garnish with more flaxseeds and almonds. Bake until golden brown and a toothpick inserted into the centers comes out clean, 25-30 min. Serve warm or at room temp.
